  "prompt": "What should every first time anime convention goer know?",
  "response": "Here are some helpful tips for first-time anime convention attendees:\n\n1. Preparation\n- Buy tickets in advance\n- Plan your cosplay or outfit\n- Bring a comfortable bag\n- Pack essentials like water, snacks, phone charger\n- Bring cash and credit cards\n- Study the convention map and schedule\n\n2. Cosplay Etiquette\n- Always ask before taking photos\n- Respect cosplayers' personal space\n- Get consent for posed/group photos\n- Compliment costumes respectfully\n\n3. Convention Behavior\n- Practice good personal hygiene\n- Be patient in lines\n- Respect event staff and volunteers\n- Stay hydrated\n- Take breaks when needed\n- Be mindful of crowded spaces\n\n4. Financial Planning\n- Budget for merchandise\n- Set spending limits\n- Bring extra money for unexpected purchases\n- Check vendor prices before buying\n\n5. Social Tips\n- Be friendly and open\n- Don't be afraid to start conversations\n- Attend panel discussions\n- Join group activities\n- Respect personal boundaries\n\n6. Practical Considerations\n- Wear comfortable shoes\n- Layer clothing\n- Bring a small first aid kit\n- Know convention security rules\n- Have a meeting spot with friends\n- Keep valuables secure\n\nEnjoy the experience and have fun!",
